#. <section class="sutta" id="mn34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn34:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 34"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 34"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn34:0.2"
msgid "Cūḷagopālakasutta"
msgstr "The Shorter Discourse on the Cowherd"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.225"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn34:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati ukkacelāyaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā tīre."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjis near Ukkacelā "
"on the bank of the Ganges river."

msgctxt "mn34:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn34:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn34:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn34:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako duppaññajātiko, vassānaṃ "
"pacchime māse saradasamaye, asamavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, "
"asamavekkhitvā pārimaṃ tīraṃ, atittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ "
"suvidehānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, there was an unintelligent Magadhan cowherd. "
"In the last month of the rainy season, without inspecting the near shore or "
"the far shore, he drove his cattle across a place with no ford on the Ganges "
"river to the land of the Suvidehans on the northern shore."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, gāvo majjhegaṅgāya nadiyā sote āmaṇḍaliyaṃ karitvā "
"tattheva anayabyasanaṃ āpajjiṃsu."
msgstr "But the cattle bunched up in mid-stream and came to ruin right there."

msgctxt "mn34:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn34:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tathā hi so, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako duppaññajātiko, vassānaṃ pacchime "
"māse saradasamaye, asamavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, "
"asamavekkhitvā pārimaṃ tīraṃ, atittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ "
"suvidehānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Because the unintelligent cowherd failed to inspect the shores before "
"driving the cattle across at a place with no ford."

#. VAR: hi keci → ye keci (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn34:3.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā akusalā imassa "
"lokassa akusalā parassa lokassa, akusalā māradheyyassa akusalā "
"amāradheyyassa, akusalā maccudheyyassa akusalā amaccudheyyassa, tesaṃ ye "
"sotabbaṃ saddahātabbaṃ maññissanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya "
"dukkhāya."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who are unskilled in this "
"world and the other world, unskilled in Māra’s dominion and its opposite, "
"and unskilled in Death’s dominion and its opposite. If anyone thinks they "
"are worth listening to and trusting, it will be for their lasting harm and "
"suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.226"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:4.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako sappaññajātiko, vassānaṃ pacchime "
"māse saradasamaye, samavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, samavekkhitvā "
"pārimaṃ tīraṃ, tittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ suvidehānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, mendicants, there was an intelligent Magadhan cowherd. In "
"the last month of the rainy season, after inspecting the near shore and the "
"far shore, he drove his cattle across a ford on the Ganges river to the land "
"of the Suvidehans on the northern shore."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:5.1"
msgid "So paṭhamaṃ patāresi ye te usabhā gopitaro gopariṇāyakā."
msgstr "First he drove across the bulls, the fathers and leaders of the herd."

msgctxt "mn34:5.2"
msgid "Te tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"They breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore."

msgctxt "mn34:5.3"
msgid "Athāpare patāresi balavagāvo dammagāvo."
msgstr "Then he drove across the strong and tractable cattle."

msgctxt "mn34:5.4"
msgid "Tepi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"They too breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore."

msgctxt "mn34:5.5"
msgid "Athāpare patāresi vacchatare vacchatariyo."
msgstr "Then he drove across the bullocks and heifers."

msgctxt "mn34:5.6"
msgid "Tepi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"They too breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore."

#. VAR: kisābalake → kisabalake (bj, pts1) | kīsabalike (s1) | kisabalike (s2, s3)
msgctxt "mn34:5.7"
msgid "Athāpare patāresi vacchake kisābalake."
msgstr "Then he drove across the calves and weak cattle."

msgctxt "mn34:5.8"
msgid "Tepi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"They too breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore."

# Almost always, bhutapubba is used for fables, thus “once upon a time”. this use is unusual, byt compare MN 36, in a similarly non-fabulous sense.
msgctxt "mn34:5.9"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, vacchako taruṇako tāvadeva jātako mātugoravakena "
"vuyhamāno, sopi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""
"Once it happened that a baby calf had just been born. Urged on by its mother’"
"s lowing, even it managed to breast the stream of the Ganges and safely "
"reach the far shore."

msgctxt "mn34:5.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn34:5.11"
msgid ""
"Tathā hi so, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako sappaññajātiko, vassānaṃ pacchime "
"māse saradasamaye, samavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, samavekkhitvā "
"pārimaṃ tīraṃ, tittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ suvidehānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Because the intelligent cowherd inspected both shores before driving the "
"cattle across at a ford."

msgctxt "mn34:5.12"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kusalā imassa "
"lokassa kusalā parassa lokassa, kusalā māradheyyassa kusalā amāradheyyassa, "
"kusalā maccudheyyassa kusalā amaccudheyyassa, tesaṃ ye sotabbaṃ "
"saddahātabbaṃ maññissanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who are skilled in this "
"world and the other world, skilled in Māra’s dominion and its opposite, and "
"skilled in Death’s dominion and its opposite. If anyone thinks they are "
"worth listening to and trusting, it will be for their lasting welfare and "
"happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:6.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye te usabhā gopitaro gopariṇāyakā te tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya "
"sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Just like the bulls, fathers and leaders of the herd, who crossed the Ganges "
"to safety"

msgctxt "mn34:6.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto "
"katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā "
"sammadaññāvimuttā, te tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṅgatā."
msgstr ""
"are the mendicants who are perfected, who have ended the defilements, "
"completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the "
"burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and "
"are rightly freed through enlightenment. Having breasted Māra’s stream, they "
"have safely crossed over to the far shore."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, balavagāvo dammagāvo tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā "
"sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Just like the strong and tractable cattle who crossed the Ganges to safety"

msgctxt "mn34:7.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā, tepi "
"tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gamissanti."
msgstr ""
"are the mendicants who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, are "
"reborn spontaneously. They’re extinguished there, and are not liable to "
"return from that world. They too, having breasted Māra’s stream, will safely "
"cross over to the far shore."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:8.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, vacchatarā vacchatariyo tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ "
"chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;"
msgstr "Just like the bullocks and heifers who crossed the Ganges to safety"

msgctxt "mn34:8.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmino sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā "
"dukkhassantaṃ karissanti, tepi tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ "
"gamissanti."
msgstr ""
"are the mendicants who, with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening "
"of greed, hate, and delusion, are once-returners. They come back to this "
"world once only, then make an end of suffering. They too, having breasted "
"Māra’s stream, will safely cross over to the far shore."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:9.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, vacchakā kisābalakā tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā "
"sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;"
msgstr "Just like the calves and weak cattle who crossed the Ganges to safety"

msgctxt "mn34:9.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyanā, tepi tiriyaṃ mārassa "
"sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gamissanti."
msgstr ""
"are the mendicants who, with the ending of three fetters are stream-"
"enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "
"They too, having breasted Māra’s stream, will safely cross over to the far "
"shore."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:10.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, vacchako taruṇako tāvadeva jātako mātugoravakena "
"vuyhamāno tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamāsi;"
msgstr ""
"Just like the baby calf who had just been born, but, urged on by its mother’"
"s lowing, still managed to cross the Ganges to safety"

msgctxt "mn34:10.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū dhammānusārino saddhānusārino, tepi "
"tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gamissanti."
msgstr ""
"are the mendicants who are followers of principles, followers by faith. They "
"too, having breasted Māra’s stream, will safely cross over to the far shore."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.227"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:11.1"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, kusalo imassa lokassa kusalo parassa lokassa, "
"kusalo māradheyyassa kusalo amāradheyyassa, kusalo maccudheyyassa kusalo "
"amaccudheyyassa. Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, ye sotabbaṃ saddahātabbaṃ "
"maññissanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Mendicants, I am skilled in this world and the other world, skilled in Māra’"
"s dominion and its opposite, and skilled in Death’s dominion and its "
"opposite. If anyone thinks I am worth listening to and trusting, it will be "
"for their lasting welfare and happiness.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:12.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn34:12.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:12.3"
msgid "“Ayaṃ loko paro loko,"
msgstr "“This world and the other world"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.4"
msgid "jānatā suppakāsito;"
msgstr "have been clearly explained by one who knows;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.5"
msgid "Yañca mārena sampattaṃ,"
msgstr "as well as Māra’s reach,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.6"
msgid "appattaṃ yañca maccunā."
msgstr "and what’s out of Death’s reach."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:12.7"
msgid "Sabbaṃ lokaṃ abhiññāya,"
msgstr "Directly knowing the whole world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.8"
msgid "sambuddhena pajānatā;"
msgstr "the Buddha who understands"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.9"
msgid "Vivaṭaṃ amatadvāraṃ,"
msgstr "has flung open the door of the deathless,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.10"
msgid "khemaṃ nibbānapattiyā."
msgstr "for realizing the sanctuary, extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn34:12.11"
msgid "Chinnaṃ pāpimato sotaṃ,"
msgstr "The Wicked One’s stream has been breasted,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.12"
msgid "Viddhastaṃ vinaḷīkataṃ;"
msgstr "it’s smashed and gutted."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn34:12.13"
msgid "Pāmojjabahulā hotha,"
msgstr "Be full of joy, mendicants,"

# Following BB in reading patthetha, comm. acknowledges both readings.
#. <br>
#. VAR: pattattha → patthetha (bj, s1-3, km, mr aṭṭhakathāyaṃ saṃ­vaṇ­ṇetab­ba­pāṭho)
msgctxt "mn34:12.14"
msgid "Khemaṃ pattattha bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "set your heart on the sanctuary!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn34:12.15"
msgid "Cūḷagopālakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
